body.description: The Rapid Care First Aid Industrial 50 Person First Aid Kit is an ANSI/OSHA approved industrial first aid kit housed in a moisture resistant wall mountable poly case. This first aid kit is perfect for job sites, office settings or home. This kit offers a varied selection of first aid supplies to assist in many emergency situations.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Rapid Care First Aid 50 Person Poly Kit - 233 Pieces About This Cabinet Rapid Care's First Aid Kit is fully compliant with ANSI Z308.1-2009 standards and meets or exceeds Federal OSHA Regulations (may vary by region). Our First Aid Kit is ideal for any job site, facility, home or office. The kit comes in a moisture resistant case. The latches on our first aid kit close securely to keep the contents in place at all times when transporting. Rapid Care is here wherever and whenever you need safety Rapid Care provides a full spectrum of first aid products that meet and exceed OSHA guidelines and ANSI standards. By choosing Rapid Care, you can rest assured your school, job site, warehouse or office is in full compliance with the most up to date standards. Always have a Rapid Care First Aid Kit wherever you are: Homes Offices Hospitals Schools Police and Fire Departments Construction Sites Manufacturing Facilities Sports & Outdoor Activities

Your Health Is Our First Priority Rapid Care offers a full line of first aid kits for every possible occasion and use. We know our products need to perform during that critical moment, be it a minor bruise on the soccer field, or a more serious injury from an auto accident. So every Rapid Care First Aid kit is designed with purpose and manufactured with care, so it will be there when you need it most. No one knows when an injury is going to happen. Keep a Rapid Care First Aid kit close at hand so you’ll be ready. Rapid Care First Aid was founded with one focus - the health and safety of our customers. We know they depend on our products to perform during every type of emergency situation. When it is needed most, Rapid care is there for its customers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 2, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Realy good kit
reviews.reviewText: Great kit with lots of product. I've already used it twice for major lacerations in my home in 2 years. Probably need to buy a replacements already. I recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wide array of products at a good value
reviews.reviewText: This kit seemed to have the most items for your buck. I needed several to put in our different fleet vehicles, tool trailer and shop. These were the most diverse. I should have bought an extra for my personal vehicle.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Has all the necessary items
reviews.reviewText: I volunteer at a homeless shelter and our first aid kits need to be OSHA certified. This kit meets that standard and has all the necessary items needed in a residential first aid kit. I also keep a kit in my car for emergencies. Good value for the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Never know when you will need first aid on the road. I keep one of these in my car, and each of my employees has one. Just in case.
